@skarabeq you are receiving that message because you are running unit tests. The test runner expects no incorrect usage notices to occur, but one did occur for the <code>register_rest_route</code> function. The test runner suppresses the normal error trigger so that it can be unit testable. If you run your code outside of PHPUnit you'll see the full <code>_doing_it_wrong</code> error.<br />
